00:14:49.620 --> 00:14:56.430
mean, the Wiki-, Wikipedia is very Internet-based,
but you might ask, "What about, what about

00:14:56.430 --> 00:15:02.110
the body?" And so, Fernanda and I started
a project, the Fleshmap project, to look at

00:15:02.110 --> 00:15:07.639
how the body is treated in various ways and
one of the first things we did is we were

00:15:07.639 --> 00:15:13.009
wondering how did people sing about the body?
How does it come up in song? And you can get

00:15:13.009 --> 00:15:18.000
data on this. You can find lyrics all over
the Internet and before we knew it we had

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:23.750
a little database of ten thousand songs and
their lyrics. They were divided into eleven

00:15:23.750 --> 00:15:31.370
genres and in a long session of brainstorming
we came up with 83 names for body parts. And

00:15:31.370 --> 00:15:36.709
we thought, "Ok, we're gonna look genre by
genre and see how often each of these body

00:15:36.709 --> 00:15:41.050
parts is mentioned." And it's no trouble at
all. To make a little computer script that

00:15:41.050 --> 00:15:46.480
does this and you can quickly compile lists
like this, for example. So, in folk songs

00:15:46.480 --> 00:15:53.339
in our sample, the word "foot" was used in
1.09 percent of our songs. Ok, not super compelling.

00:15:53.339 --> 00:15:59.390
You can make a bar graph; it's not very compelling,
either. But what's interesting is that when

00:15:59.390 --> 00:16:05.199
you start to graph it using imagery--and we
found a great place to get some sort of stock

00:16:05.199 --> 00:16:11.889
photography that we could use for this-- suddenly
you start to see what's going on. So, here

00:16:11.889 --> 00:16:16.470
you're looking at a bubble chart so each body
part is sized; the area is proportional to

00:16:16.470 --> 00:16:20.910
how often it comes up. So, you can see that
in folk music it's sort of eye and hand and

00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:26.300
face music with a little bit of lips and some
knees and ears. And it makes you wonder, "What

00:16:26.300 --> 00:16:32.449
about other genres?" Well, let's take a look
at blues. It's also very simple, like a lot

00:16:32.449 --> 00:16:37.449
